    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1977-05-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1977-05-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="123"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d123">
                <head>123. Memorandum From the Acting Assistant Secretary of State for
                    Administration (Dikeos) to the Deputy Under Secretary of State for Management
                        (<persName corresp="#p_MRM_1">Moose</persName>)<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d123fn1">Source: National Archives, RG 59, Records of the Under
                        Secretary for Management (M), 1977–1978, Box 1, Chron May 1977. No
                        classification marking.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1977-05-06">May 6, 1977</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Employment Ceilings</item>
                </list>
                <p>We have been informally advised by <gloss target="#t_OMB_1">OMB</gloss> that the
                    government-wide employment reduction package will go forward to the President
                        <pb facs="0531" n="502" xml:id="pg_502"/> shortly. The <gloss
                        target="#t_OMB_1">OMB</gloss> recommendation to the President for the
                    Department’s full-time permanent employment ceiling will probably be as
                    follows:</p>
                <p rend="center">Full-Time Permanent Employment Ceilings</p>
                <table cols="3">
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>
                            <gloss target="#t_FY_1">FY</gloss>-1977</cell>
                        <cell>
                            <gloss target="#t_FY_1">FY</gloss>-1978</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Total (including supplementals)</cell>
                        <cell role="num">22,920</cell>
                        <cell role="num">23,041</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Proposed reduction</cell>
                        <cell role="num">−300</cell>
                        <cell role="num">−375</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>End-of-year employment ceiling</cell>
                        <cell role="num">22,620</cell>
                        <cell role="num">22,666</cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p>This represents a further reduction of 50 from the earlier <gloss
                        target="#t_OMB_1">OMB</gloss> International Affairs Division proposal.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d123fn2">Not found.</note> The figures also do not reflect 76
                    reimbursable positions (mostly <gloss target="#t_AID_1">AID</gloss> transfer of
                    functions and program build-up) which should be added by <gloss
                        target="#t_OMB_1">OMB</gloss> to our total.</p>
                <p>It appears that an employment ceiling reduction of this magnitude would require
                    abolishing approximately 200 positions currently authorized to the bureaus.</p>
                <p>Our full-time permanent employment as of March 31 was 22,673. We should have end
                    of April employment figures within two weeks.</p>
            </div>
